URL Shortener - Django Project
==============================

Project Name: URL Shortner
GitHub Repo: https://github.com/vishnuvm1122/url-shortner

Description:
-------------
This is a Django-based URL Shortener application. It allows users to:
- Create short URLs for long URLs
- Track the number of clicks per URL
- Manage URLs in a simple dashboard
- Redirect short URLs to the original long URLs

Features:
----------
1. User authentication and dashboard
2. Create and manage shortened URLs
3. Click count tracking for each URL
4. Simple and responsive UI using Bootstrap

Technologies Used:
------------------
- Python 3.8+
- Django 3.x/4.x
- SQLite/PostgreSQL (optional)
- Bootstrap 5 for front-end styling
- HTML, CSS, JS

Setup Instructions:
-------------------
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/vishnuvm1122/url-shortner.git

2. Navigate into the project folder:
   cd url-shortner

3. Create a virtual environment:
   python3 -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate  (Linux/macOS)
   venv\Scripts\activate     (Windows)

4. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

5. Apply migrations:
   python manage.py migrate

6. Create a superuser (admin):
   python manage.py createsuperuser

7. Run the development server:
   python manage.py runserver

8. Open your browser at:
   http://127.0.0.1:8000/

Notes:
------
- Make sure to set your GitHub personal access token if pushing via HTTPS.
- For production, configure proper database and environment settings.
